    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In this post I’ll explain how you can leverage an <em>static site generator</em> to<br>create and maintain your own blog.</p><h2 id="What-is-an-static-site-generator"><a href="#What-is-an-static-site-generator" class="headerlink" title="What is an static site generator?"></a>What is an static site generator?</h2><p>First things first. There are plenty of generators and <a href="https://www.staticgen.com" target="_blank" rel="external">here</a><br>you can find a good plethora of them.</p><h3 id="How-to-create-a-new-post"><a href="#How-to-create-a-new-post" class="headerlink" title="How to create a new post"></a>How to create a new post</h3><p>From a terminal just type:</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">$ hexo new <span class="string">"Terrific Title for a Blog Post"</span></div></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>I hope you have found this an interesting post. I’ll love to see your comments below.</p><p><strong> Wait a minute! Comments? In an static page?? Are you kidding me??? </strong></p><p>Ouch.</p>]]></content>
    
